[4]
Date: 22 Dec 2008
From: Heli Siikamaki


We have had 2 more Finnish tourists with falciparum malaria from
Gambia in December 2008 after writing the Eurosurveillance articles;
the same story: no appropriate prophylaxis.

--
Heli Siikamaki
Helsinki
Finland

******
[5] Spain
Date: 22 Dec 2008
Source: TropMEDnet [edited]
<http://www.bctropen.de>


We know of a cluster of 3 imported malaria cases (one fatal case) in
a group of returning travelers from the Gambia seen at a secondary
hospital in Madrid. None was on prophylaxis.

[Rogelio Lopez-Velez, Madrid, Spain]

--
Communicated by:
Tomas Jelinek
<jelinek@bctropen.de>
TropNetEurop coordinator
Berlin Center for Travel and Tropical Medicine
Jagerstr. 67-69, 10117 Berlin, Germany
<http://www.bctropen.de>

[ProMED thanks Tomas Jelinek from TropNetEurop for permission to
publish the additional cases from Sweden, Finland and Spain, bringing
the total number of reported cases to 64 with 3 fatalities. None of
the new cases took malaria prophylaxis.

The comment from Dr David Conway that the distribution of malaria in
The Gambia is patchy makes detailed investigation of the movements in
The Gambia of the patients and mapping of the hotels where they
stayed important. However, The Gambia is known as a malaria endemic
destination, and the fact that very few had been recommended malaria
chemoprophylaxis by the travel agent who sold the travel highlight
that this situation can only be prevented in the future by travel
agents taking responsibility for information on health issues at the
destination.

Maps of The Gambia are available at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/gambia.gif>
and the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?v=13.5,-15.5,6>.
- Mod.EP]
